column22: The geochemical data reproducibility of the sediment samples could have been the major reason not to proceed with interpretation followed by publication. The poor reproducibility of data (accuracy and precision) may lead to spurious data and its trends which might lead to erroneous past climate reconstruction.

column24: We are very rigorous in presenting methods in scientific articles, but because we are using mostly qualitative data, which requires sensitive insightful handling by knowledgeable and skilled researchers, we do not publish detailed data, such as transcripts, particularly since participants often seek acknowledgement, rather than anonymity, because they trust us and want recognition of their contribution to the knowledge produced. We know we have developed the guidelines to respect this trust and intentions, but would require further consent to hand data forward to other researchers who are not known to participants.
